From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Rurix Godot Bridge <rurix@example.invalid>
Date: Wed, 8 Jul 2026 19:50:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Scaffold the GRX-009 real-pass result writeback for the
 luminance level-0 dispatch

Stacked on 0001-rurix-accel-module-scaffold.patch,
0002-rurix-accel-luminance-pass-gate.patch,
0003-rurix-accel-luminance-core-callsite-wiring.patch,
0004-rurix-accel-luminance-resource-mapping-scaffold.patch,
0005-rurix-accel-luminance-runtime-binding-preflight.patch,
0006-rurix-accel-luminance-gated-dispatch-bringup.patch,
0007-rurix-accel-luminance-native-resource-handle-mapping.patch,
0008-rurix-accel-luminance-godot-runtime-bridge-recording-smoke.patch, and
0009-rurix-accel-luminance-real-pass-optin.patch. This stage A5 patch is a
result writeback SCAFFOLD only: it wires what happens at the Auto Exposure
call site AFTER the opt-in real-pass arm (dispatch_real_pass) actually
returned RXGD_STATUS_OK from a real recorded level-0 dispatch.

- servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp Auto Exposure
  call site: when try_record_luminance_reduction() returned true on the
  real-pass arm, the Rurix bridge has already dispatched the level-0
  reduction INTO the real luminance_buffers->reduce[0] ID3D12Resource*
  resolved in segment 4e, so the level-0 result is physically written back
  into Godot's own reduce pyramid storage. The scaffold prints a
  machine-readable RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_LUMINANCE_REAL_PASS_WRITEBACK marker
  recording that writeback, then deliberately clears
  rurix_recorded_luminance so the FULL native Godot luminance path still
  runs as the continuation/backstop: multi-level pyramid, EMA feedback,
  previous-luminance double buffering, and the final WRITE_LUMINANCE
  clamp/min/max level are not yet parity-proven on the Rurix side
  (math_parity_evidence.json is level-0 CPU-proven, pending GPU), so the
  native path re-renders every level and the rendered image can never
  change while the scaffold is in place.

- modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp: the segment 4d/4f
  RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_LUMINANCE_RECORD marker is now printed only under the
  harness-only dispatch_recording_smoke opt-in, so a real-pass success on
  the dispatch_real_pass arm is reported by the
  RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_LUMINANCE_REAL_PASS marker alone and is never
  misreported as a recording-smoke run (the segment 4h harness treats the
  RECORD marker as an integrity failure).

Replacing the native continuation (actually skipping native level 0 and
running only the remaining native levels off the Rurix-written reduce[0])
belongs to the multi-level continuation round and requires measured GPU
math-parity evidence first. This patch does not change RXGD_ABI_VERSION,
does not enable any per-pass setting by default, does not alter the
fail-closed bridge semantics, and makes no visual, measured-telemetry,
GPU-timestamp, or performance claim by itself.
---
diff --git a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
index 10f99e0..7c41b02 100644
--- a/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
+++ b/modules/rurix_accel/rurix_accel.cpp
@@ -307,7 +307,13 @@ bool RurixAccelD3D12Hooks::try_record_luminance_reduction(uint64_t p_source_nati
 	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/luminance_reduction/dispatch_real_pass")) {
 		print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_LUMINANCE_REAL_PASS: pass=RXGD_PASS_LUMINANCE_REDUCTION dispatched=1");
 	}
-	print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_LUMINANCE_RECORD: pass=RXGD_PASS_LUMINANCE_REDUCTION recorded=1");
+	// GRX-009 stage A5: the RECORD marker belongs to the segment 4d/4f
+	// harness-only recording smoke; print it only under that opt-in so a
+	// real-pass success on the dispatch_real_pass arm is never misreported
+	// as a recording-smoke run.
+	if (GLOBAL_GET("rendering/rurix_accel/passes/luminance_reduction/dispatch_recording_smoke")) {
+		print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_LUMINANCE_RECORD: pass=RXGD_PASS_LUMINANCE_REDUCTION recorded=1");
+	}
 	return true;
 }
 
diff --git a/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp b/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp
index c393ffe..5b20d17 100644
--- a/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp
+++ b/servers/rendering/renderer_rd/renderer_scene_render_rd.cpp
@@ -589,6 +589,21 @@ void RendererSceneRenderRD::_render_buffers_post_process_and_tonemap(const Rende
 			if (rurix_source_native_handle != 0 && rurix_dest_native_handle != 0) {
 				rurix_recorded_luminance = D3D12Hooks::get_singleton()->try_record_luminance_reduction(rurix_source_native_handle, (uint32_t)MAX(rurix_source_size.x, 0), (uint32_t)MAX(rurix_source_size.y, 0), rurix_dest_native_handle, (uint32_t)rurix_dest_size.x, (uint32_t)rurix_dest_size.y, auto_exposure_max_sensitivity, auto_exposure_min_sensitivity, (float)step);
 			}
+			if (rurix_recorded_luminance) {
+				// GRX-009 stage A5 result writeback SCAFFOLD. The Rurix bridge
+				// dispatched the level-0 reduction directly into the real
+				// luminance_buffers->reduce[0] ID3D12Resource*, so the level-0
+				// result is already written back into Godot's reduce pyramid
+				// storage. Record that writeback with a machine-readable
+				// marker, then keep the FULL native Godot luminance path as
+				// the continuation/backstop: multi-level pyramid, EMA, prev
+				// luminance, and the final WRITE_LUMINANCE clamp level are not
+				// yet parity-proven on the Rurix side, so the native path
+				// re-renders every level and the image can never change while
+				// this scaffold is in place.
+				print_line("RXGD_GODOT_RUNTIME_LUMINANCE_REAL_PASS_WRITEBACK: level0_dst=reduce[0] native_continuation=active scaffold=1");
+				rurix_recorded_luminance = false;
+			}
 		}
 #endif
 		if (!rurix_recorded_luminance) {
-- 
